<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E802513E7D6AFA133BD2F8F9" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE802513E7D6AFA133BD2F8F9" blockId="2.[828,1437,1479,2078]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7D6AFA133CF5FA39" bold="true" box="[828,948,1479,1502]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male body length 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7AC4FA133BBAFA39" box="[1170,1275,1479,1502]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.84" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="2.84">2.84 mm</quantity>
. Antennomere 9 with round, deep ventral concavity in apical half; antennomere 10 strongly constricted at base and forming nodule-like stem, broadly impressed for most area of ventral side. Horn-like metaventral processes in lateral view slightly broaden at apices. Protrochanter with blunt ventral projection, protibia with small tubercle at apex; mesotrochanter with small triangular protuberance. Median lobe of aedeagus almost symmetric dorsoventrally; parameres thin and elongate; endophallus with seven sclerites and one structure. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E802513F7D6AF8F33B6AFEB2" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE802513F7D6AF8F33B70FED2" blockId="2.[828,1437,1479,2078]" lastBlockId="3.[828,1437,190,565]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7D6AF8F33B42F8D9" bold="true" box="[828,1027,1831,1854]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
Description. 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E802513E7D9DF8F33B42F8D9" bold="true" box="[971,1027,1831,1854]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Male</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="134396FEE802513E7A46F8F33B21F8D9" box="[1040,1120,1831,1854]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[151,182,2057,2076]" captionTargetBox="[258,1324,1020,2034]" captionTargetId="figure-392@1.[255,1333,1017,2038]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Dorsal habitus of Labomimus males. A – L. cavicornis sp. nov.; B – L. cucphuong sp. nov. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037466/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7AADF8F33A1DF8D9" box="[1275,1372,1831,1854]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.84" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="2.84">2.84 mm</quantity>
. Head winder than long, HL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7A7CF8933BCDF8B9" box="[1066,1164,1863,1886]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.48">0.48 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE802513E7A9DF8933A6FF8B9" box="[1227,1326,1863,1886]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.56">0.56 mm</quantity>
; eyes prominent, each composed of about 43 facets. Antennomeres 3–8 gradually becoming shorter, antennomeres 9–11 (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE802513E7B27F8533C1CF859" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[201,1397,612,1980]" captionTargetId="figure-199@4.[189,1398,612,1986]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cucphuong sp. nov.A – right antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037472/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) forming distinct club; antennomere 9 with round, deep ventral concavity in apical half, antennomere 10 strongly constricted near base and forming nodule-like stem, most part of ventral surface broadly impressed, antennomere 11 much shorter than 10, truncate at base and with round apex. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE803513F7F5DFF0A3E1BFF12" box="[267,346,222,245]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[201,1397,612,1980]" captionTargetId="figure-199@4.[189,1398,612,1986]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cucphuong sp. nov.A – right antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037472/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
) slightly longer than wide, PL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE803513F7CC3FF0A3DB5FF12" box="[661,756,222,245]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="0.56">0.56 mm</quantity>
, PW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE803513F7E9FFF2A3E6CFEF2" box="[201,301,254,277]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.50 mm</quantity>
, narrowed anteriorly at apical 2/5. Elytra broader than long, EL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE803513F7FD1FECA3EA8FED2" box="[391,489,286,309]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="0.74">0.74 mm</quantity>
, EW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE803513F7C75FECA3DC7FED2" box="[547,646,286,309]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="1.05">1.05 mm</quantity>
. Horn-like metaventral processes (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE803513F7FC1FEEA3EADFEB2" box="[407,492,318,341]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[201,1397,612,1980]" captionTargetId="figure-199@4.[189,1398,612,1986]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cucphuong sp. nov.A – right antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037472/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
) in lateral view slightly expand at apices. Protrochanter (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE803513F7FA3FE8A3D09FE92" box="[501,584,350,373]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[201,1397,612,1980]" captionTargetId="figure-199@4.[189,1398,612,1986]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cucphuong sp. nov.A – right antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037472/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
) with blunt projection; profemur angularly expanded at middle; protibia (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE803513F7EC9FE4A3FACFE52" box="[159,237,414,437]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[201,1397,612,1980]" captionTargetId="figure-199@4.[189,1398,612,1986]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cucphuong sp. nov.A – right antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037472/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
) with small tubercle at apex; mesotrochanter (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE803513F7C9BFE4A3FF5FE32" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[201,1397,612,1980]" captionTargetId="figure-199@4.[189,1398,612,1986]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cucphuong sp. nov.A – right antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037472/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
) with short triangle protuberance; mesofemur (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE803513F7CCBFE6A3DAAFE32" box="[669,747,446,469]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[201,1397,612,1980]" captionTargetId="figure-199@4.[189,1398,612,1986]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cucphuong sp. nov.A – right antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037472/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
), metatrochanter and metafemur (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE803513F7FB5FE0A3D72FE12" box="[483,563,478,501]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[201,1397,612,1980]" captionTargetId="figure-199@4.[189,1398,612,1986]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cucphuong sp. nov.A – right antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037472/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
) simple. Abdomen broad at base and narrowed apically, AL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE803513F7C60FE2A3DD4FDF2" box="[566,661,510,533]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="0.96">0.96 mm</quantity>
, AW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE803513F7C9CFE2A3F85FDD2" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.07" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="1.07">1.07 mm</quantity>
. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE803513F7F1EFDCA3EFBFDD2" box="[328,442,542,565]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[151,182,2006,2025]" captionTargetBox="[201,1397,612,1980]" captionTargetId="figure-199@4.[189,1398,612,1986]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Male diagnostic features of Labomimus cucphuong sp. nov.A – right antennal club, in ventral view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H–J – aedeagus, in dorsal (H), lateral (I), and ventral (J) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, H, I, J; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037472/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Figs 3H–J</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4C80279EE803513F7F9CFDCA3D6BFDD2" box="[458,554,542,565]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="0.51">0.51 mm</quantity>
long; median lobe almost symmetric dorsoventrally, in lateral view curved and narrowed at apex; each paramere with two preapical setae; endophallus composed of seven sclerites and one membranous structure.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE803513F7D0CFEEA3B6AFEB2" blockId="3.[828,1437,190,565]" box="[858,1067,318,341]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
