<emphasis id="B90C5669E803513F7D0CFEEA3CECFEB2" bold="true" box="[858,941,318,341]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Female</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E803513F7D6AFE8A3BB6FE52" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE803513F7D6AFE8A3BB6FE52" blockId="3.[828,1437,190,565]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E803513F7D6AFE8A3B5BFE92" bold="true" box="[828,1050,350,373]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
This species can be readily recognized and distinguished from all other members of the genus by uniquely modified male antennal club.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
